Singapore welcomed the London MetalExchange's (LME) decision to list Singapore as a delivery pointfor the LME's new dollar-denominated aluminium contract.    Tay Thiam Peng, manager for international trading at theTrade Development Board, said the decision would boostSingapore's image as a major delivery port.    "We hope this will encourage more metal traders to set upshop here and that Singapore can become a delivery port forother metals as well," he said.    The new contract, to start trading on June 1, is LME'sfirst dollar-contract. REUTER&#3;